<li><strong style="color: var(--atext);">2021 Febuary 20th (210220)</strong> <em>- &ldquo;Media player&rdquo; Update 4</em>
<ul>
<li><strong>Media Player Accessability changes;</strong><br />
<ul>
<li>Added links dropdown menu which includes the current playlist link (if there is any) and original video source.</li>
<li>Rewind and fastforward times can now be changed through the Links dropdown menu in incriments of 5 seconds.</li>
<li>Video skip times are now capped between 5 seconds and 60.</li>
<li>Fastforwarding or rewinding now updates the video timeline.</li>
<li>If a video does not belong in a playlist, the Previous and Next video buttons are disabled and grayed out.</li>
<li>Added more statuses in the console alongside fake delays to emulate windows processing.</li>
<li><em>Media handling optimisation.</em></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Replaced the Help Button redirect on windows with the Embedded Media Player Instructional Video, which will brind up the mediaplayer with included video.</li>
</ul>
<ol>
<li>- Fast forwarding past the duration of the video now plays the next video instead of moving the progression bar along and THEN skipping to the next video.</li>
<li>- Skipping to the next or previous video now resets the timeline before playing instead of waiting for youtube to push a timestamp update.</li>
<li><em>- Fixed graphical imperfections with the taskbar icon dividers.</em></li>
<li><em>- Fixed a few bugs to do with addressing handles that don&rsquo;t exist yet.</em></li>
</ol></li>
<li><strong style="color: var(--atext);">2021 Febuary 18th (210218)</strong> <em>- &ldquo;Media player</em><em>&rdquo; Update 3.1</em>
